      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "@ohos.multimedia.mediaLibrary",
      "purpose": "Deprecated media library API — replaced by photoAccessHelper",
      "anchor": "ohosmultimediamedialibrary已废弃",
      "status": "missing"
    },
    {
      "name": "Writing tools (WriteToGallery)",
      "purpose": "Write encoded image bytes to a gallery asset URI obtained via SaveButton or createAsset",
      "anchor": "writing-tools-writetogallery",
      "status": "found"
    }
  ],
  "notableFindings": [
    "@ohos.multimedia.mediaLibrary is fully deprecated; all new code must use @ohos.file.photoAccessHelper from @kit.MediaLibraryKit",
    "CanvasRenderingContext2D.getPixelMap() directly returns a PixelMap — prefer this over toDataURL + decoding for the encode-save pipeline",
    "The recommended privacy-preserving flow is: SaveButton (grants temp permission) -> createAsset (returns writable URI) -> fileIo.write (writes encoded bytes)",
    "ImagePacker.packToData() accepts PixelMap (not just ImageSource), so Canvas.getPixelMap() feeds directly into the encoding step",
    "createAssetWithShortTermPermission() grants 5-minute write window without a visible security control button"
  ],
  "missingApis": [
    "@ohos.multimedia.mediaLibrary"
  ]
}
